The first plot I created represents the data from Washington State Department of Ecology Water Quality Data. Using this dataset from the Washington Department of Ecology, I wanted to see how water quality during the summer of 2016. This was at the tail-end of a few summers of harmful algal bloom outbreaks, so I want to see how water quality was different in a few areas of the Puget Sound. I did not separate the locations in the same graph here, but will do so in the next plot.

This plot above represents the same data that I isolated from the 2016 for the three locations: Elliot Bay, Puget Sound Basin, and Port Townsend. The plot above, however, uses facet_wrap to separate the three locations in visualization.

This plot above shows the x and y axis switched from the previous two, representin the pH and depth of the three sites that were surveyed.
